      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"1. HOT ASHES steps out for the first time at this track. Missed the frame last time when 4th and beaten 10 lengths (26.28) at Murray Bridge. Boasts two wins from three starts out of this box. Looks the one to beat on his best form. 7. ODDLY COOL charged out of the boxes with a strong early split and went straight to the front, scoring an all the way win (22.96) over 400m at Warragul. Hard to knock his form from this box, unbeaten in two starts. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. 2. MIDNIGHT THUNDER found the frame for the second consecutive time when narrowly beaten into second last time out (23.55) over 410m at Horsham. Can turn it around this time. 3. ZERO KILLER is always hard to beat when drawn in this box.\",\"runners\":[1,7,2,3],\"exclusive\":false}",
